text: KidsTv.
Well boom buddies, it’s been a loooong night taking care of the twins.
Your little baby brother and sister are sooooo cute!
Yeah, but now it’s waaay past their bedtime!
Ok, come on little babies, time to get some sleep.
I know - let’s sing the lullaby that my mommy sings, to help the twins get reeeeal sleepy...
Good idea!....
Rock-a-bye, baby on the treetop
When the wind blows the cradle will rock
If the bough breaks the cradle will fall
But buddies will catch you cradle and all
Hey, you naughty twins!
Oh geez, that didn’t go so well, did it?!
Pleeeease go to sleep!
Hey, let us try!!!
Babies are sleepy cozy and fair
Mama she sings in her rocking chair
Forward and back she rocks and she swings
And when we’re asleep we hears what she sings
Oh boy, will these little twins ever sleep?
I hope so.
Ok little girl, back into bed you go….
We’ll sing you a liiiiittle bit more …..
Hush a bye babies up in the sky
On a soft cloud it’s easy to fly
Angels watch over us as we sleep
So hush a bye babies don’t make a peep
Ohhhh noooo!
Ok guys. one more time.
Let’s get both of twins to sleep at last!
Rock a bye babies don’t ever fear
Never you worry buddies are near
Cosy in bed eyes are shut tight

So sleep now Sweet Babies
Till morning light
HMMMMMM. NIGHT NIGHT BOOM BUDDIES.
